cru - Crucible CLI - Interactive knowledge management with semantic search

Usage: cru [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  chat         Interactive AI chat with session persistence and tool access [aliases: c]
  mcp          Start MCP server exposing Crucible tools for external AI agents
  process      Process markdown files through the pipeline (parse, enrich, store) [aliases: p]
  search       Search kiln notes using semantic and/or text search
  stats        Display kiln statistics
  models       List available models from configured LLM provider
  config       Manage Crucible configuration (initialize, view, export) [aliases: cfg]
  status       Display storage status and statistics for the knowledge base
  doctor       Run installation diagnostics for Crucible
  storage      Manage storage operations (migration, verification, backup, cleanup)
  agents       Manage agent cards (list, show, validate)
  tasks        Manage tasks from a TASKS.md file (list, next, pick, done)
  workflow     Inspect workflow notes in the active kiln (list, show)
  daemon       Manage the Crucible daemon (start, stop, status, logs)
  skills       Discover and manage agent skills (list, show, search)
  tools        Discover and manage tools (list, show)
  plugin       Manage and develop Lua plugins
  lua          Evaluate Lua code in the daemon's plugin runtime
  init         Initialize a new kiln or project [aliases: i]
  session      Manage chat sessions (create, configure, send, pause, resume, end) [aliases: s, sess]
  auth         Manage LLM provider credentials (login, logout, list)
  set          Configure a running session's settings (same syntax as TUI :set)
  setup        Bootstrap the Crucible runtime (plugins, themes, default init.lua)
  completions  Generate shell completion scripts for bash, zsh, and fish
  web          Start the web UI server for browser-based chat
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -l, --log-level <LOG_LEVEL>
          Set log level (off, error, warn, info, debug, trace) If not specified, uses config file value or defaults to 'off'

          Possible values:
          - off:   No logging output
          - error: Error messages only
          - warn:  Warnings and errors
          - info:  Informational messages (default for verbose)
          - debug: Debug messages
          - trace: Trace-level messages (most verbose)

  -v, --verbose
          Enable verbose logging (shortcut for --log-level=debug)

  -C, --config <CONFIG>
          Config file path (defaults to ~/.config/crucible/config.toml)

      --embedding-url <EMBEDDING_URL>
          Embedding service URL (overrides config file)

      --embedding-model <EMBEDDING_MODEL>
          Embedding model name (overrides config file)

  -f, --format <FORMAT>
          Set output format (table, json, csv)
          
          [default: table]

      --standalone
          Run with an in-process daemon (no background server required). Useful for single-session use, restricted environments, or testing. Data persists to the kiln's .crucible/ directory

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version
